data.name: BasicSettingsHelp.Text
data.value: In this section, you can set up the basic settings for this page.

data.name: TabNameHelp.Text
data.value: This is the name of the Page. The text you enter will be displayed in the menu system.

data.name: TitleHelp.Text
data.value: Enter a title for the Page here. The text you enter will be displayed in the browser window title.

data.name: DescriptionHelp.Text
data.value: Enter a description about this page here.

data.name: ParentTab.Help
data.value: Select the page that you would like this page to be a child of.

data.name: UrlHelp.Text
data.value: If you would like this page to behave as a navigation link to another resource, you can specify the Link URL value here. Please note that this field is optional.

data.name: CopyModulesHelp.Text
data.value: Select the page (if any) that you would like to copy modules from.

data.name: CopyContentHelp.Text
data.value: Select the modules that you wish to copy and enter the title for the module. In addition specify if you want to create a New module ( without content ), a Copy of the module ( with content ), or a Reference to an existing module ( shared content ).

data.name: AdvancedSettingsHelp.Text
data.value: In this section, you can set up more advanced settings for this page.

data.name: IconHelp.Text
data.value: You can choose an icon that can be used in the menu.

data.name: plSkin.Help
data.value: The selected skin will be applied to this page.

data.name: plContainer.Help
data.value: The selected container will be applied to all modules on this page.

data.name: MenuHelp.Text
data.value: You have the choice on whether or not to include the page in the main navigation menu. If a page is not included in the menu, you can still link to it based on its page URL.

data.name: DisabledHelp.Text
data.value: If the page is disabled it cannot be clicked in any navigation menu. This option is used to provide place-holders for child menu items.

data.name: PermissionsHelp.Text
data.value: Choose the groups of people that can view and administer this page.

data.name: KeyWordsHelp.Text
data.value: Enter some keywords for this page (separated by commas). These keywords are used by some internet search engines like Google to help index your site's pages.

data.name: plSecure.Help
data.value: Specify whether or not this page should be forced to use a secure connection (SSL). This option will only be enabled if the administrator has Enabled SSL in the site settings.

data.name: plStartDate.Help
data.value: Enter the start date for displaying this page. You may use the Calendar to pick a date.

data.name: plEndDate.Help
data.value: Enter the end date for displaying this page. You may use the Calendar to pick a date.

data.name: DeleteSpecialPage.Text
data.value: A page defined as Home, Splash, Login or User Page for the website, or the last visible Page in the website cannot be deleted. Also the Admin and Host Page can not be deleted.

data.name: ModuleHelp.Text
data.value:
Page Management

This module allows you to modify the settings for an existing page, delete the page, or submit it to Google for indexing.

data.name: RefreshInterval.Help
data.value: Enter the interval to wait between automatic page refeshes. (Example: Enter "60" for 1 minute or leave blank to disable.)

data.name: PageHeadText.Help
data.value: Enter any tags (i.e. META tags) that should be rendered in the "HEAD" tag of the HTML for this page.

data.name: plCopySkin.Help
data.value: Copies the currently selected design (skin and container) for the page to descendant pages. Option only available to Website Admins and SuperUsers.

data.name: plCopyPerm.Help
data.value: Copies the currently selected permissions for the page to descendant pages.

data.name: ExceededQuota.Text
data.value: Adding this page will exceed the Page Quota for this site. Please contact your hosting provider for inquiries related to increasing your Page Quota.

data.name: plFolder.Help
data.value: Select the template folder to use

data.name: plTemplate.Help
data.value: Select a page template which you would like to use to create this page.

data.name: DesignCopyError.Text
data.value: There was an error copying the design

data.name: PermissionCopyError.Text
data.value: There was an error copying the permissions

data.name: TabExists.Text
data.value: The Page Name you chose is already being used for another page at the same level of the page hierarchy.

data.name: InsertPosition.Help
data.value: Select the page that you would like this page to be inserted before or after, or optionally add the page to end of the current level.

data.name: InvalidTabName.Text
data.value: This is an invalid Page Name

data.name: valEndDate2.ErrorMessage
data.value: End Date must be after Start Date

data.name: plPermanentRedirect.Help
data.value: Check this box if you want to notify the client that this page should be considered as permanently moved. This would allow SearchEngines to modify their URLs to directly link to the resource. This is ignored if the LinkType is None.

data.name: plPriority.Help
data.value: Enter the desired priority (between 0 and 1.0). This helps determine how this page is ranked in Google with respect to other pages on your site (0.5 is the default).

data.name: DeletePermissionError.Text
data.value: You don't have permission to delete this page.

data.name: IconLargeHelp.Text
data.value: You can choose a large icon that will be used in the console.

data.name: TabRecycled.Text
data.value: A page with this name exists in the Recycle Bin. To restore this page use the Recycle Bin.

data.name: InvalidTabDates.Text
data.value: You have entered Invalid Start and End dates - the page will never display.

data.name: CacheProvider.Help
data.value: Select the provider to use for this page.

data.name: CacheDuration.Help
data.value: Enter the duration (in seconds) to cache the page for. This must be an integer.

data.name: CacheMaxVaryByCount.Help
data.value: Enter the maximum number of variations to cache for this page. This must be an integer. (Note, this feature prevents potential denial of service attacks.)

data.name: CacheIncludeExclude.Help
data.value: If set to INCLUDE, all querystring parameter value variations will result in a new item in the output cache. If set to EXCLUDE, querystring parameters will not be used to vary the cached page.

data.name: IncludeVaryBy.Help
data.value: A list of querystring parameter names (separated by commas) to be INCLUDED in the variations of cached pages. This setting is only valid when the default above is set to EXCLUDE querystring parameters from cached page variations.

data.name: ExcludeVaryBy.Help
data.value: A list of querystring parameter names (separated by commas) to be EXCLUDED from the variations of cached pages. This setting is only valid when the default above is set to INCLUDE querystring parameters from cached page variations.

data.name: lblCachedItemCount.Text
data.value: Current Cache Count: {0} variations for this page

data.name: valCacheTime.ErrorMessage
data.value: Cache Duration must be a number

data.name: valCacheVaryByLimit.ErrorMessage
data.value: Cache Vary ByLimit must be a number

data.name: CacheDurationInfo.Text
data.value: Note, there is a Scheduled Task for purging the Output Cache. The task must run more frequently than the Cache Duration you specify here.

data.name: BadTemplate.Text
data.value: The page template is not a valid xml document. Please select a different template and try again.

data.name: plTags.Help
data.value: Select items from the drop-down to tag this Page.

data.value: You are about to mark this page as translated? The action is immediate. Are you sure?

data.name: UnTranslateConfirm.Text
data.value: You are about to mark this page as not translated? The action is immediate. Are you sure?

data.name: cultureTypeLabel.Help
data.value: Select whether this is a culture neutral page which is the same in all languages or should have localized versions for each language.

data.name: DefaultCulture.Text

data.name: Localize.Confirm

data.name: PublishPage.Text

data.value: This will delete all translated version of the page. Only the default culture version of the page will remain. Are you sure you want to do this?

data.value: A stylesheet that will only be loaded for this page. The file must be located in the home directory or a sub folder of the current website.

data.value: Check this box to ensure that this page is excluded from any rules that may end up in a redirect.
